 and histological review of 51 patients. <em>J Hepatol</em>1986; 2: 141–156.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1016/S0168-8278(86)80073-3">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/3958471/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=J+Hepatol&amp;publication_year=1986&amp;pages=141&amp;doi=10.1016%2FS0168-8278%2886%2980073-3&amp;pmid=3958471">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">4.</div><div id="R4" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content"><span class="named-content" data-type="arthw-firstauthor"><span class="named-content" data-type="arthw-snm">Desmet</span><span class="named-content" data-type="arthw-fnm">VJ</span></span>. Congenital diseases of intrahepatic bile ducts: variations on the theme “ductal plate malformation.” <em>Hepatology</em>1992; 16: 1069–1083.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1002/hep.1840160434">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/1398487/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Hepatology&amp;publication_year=1992&amp;pages=1069&amp;doi=10.1002%2Fhep.1840160434&amp;pmid=1398487">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">5.</div><div id="R5" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content"><span class="named-content" data-type="arthw-firstauthor"><span class="named-content" data-type="arthw-snm">Krause</span><span class="named-content" data-type="arthw-fnm">D</span></span>, Cercueil JP, Dranssart M, Cognet F, Piard F, Hillon P. MRI for evaluating congenital bile duct abnormalities. <em>J Comput Assist Tomogr<